author: Sarah Burns
title: Ten women who attended Dublin maternity hospital tested positive for coronavirus
description: Master of Rotunda says patients should be reassured there are no proven cases of transmission from mother to baby during pregnancy
content:
Up to 10 women who have tested positive for coronavirus have attended the Rotunda maternity hospital in Dublin.
Some of them were outpatients, and remain well in the outpatient setting, a spokesperson for the hospital said.
